# Security headers for Netlify (and Cloudflare Pages) deployments.
# GitHub Pages cannot set response headers; there the CSP ships via the
# <meta http-equiv> tag SvelteKit injects into every prerendered page,
# and the headers below simply do not apply.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=()
